    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen you give a count to `zb` it behaves the same way if you were to pass in a count to `zt`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1.  open up a text file that is long enough\n2.  scrol down a few times `C-d`\n3.  press `10zb`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe buffer should be redrawn so that the line on step 3 is 10 lines from the bottom of the window, instead it is 10 lines from the top of the window (as it should be if we used `zt`)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 11.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBrew",
